I"Ÿ<p>Kill <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">make</code>.</p>

<p>Kill <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">npm</code>.</p>

<p>Kill package managers.</p>

<p>Kill libraries.</p>

<p>Kill synchrony.</p>

<h2 id="goal---zero-dependencies">Goal - Zero Dependencies</h2>

<p>Aim to write software that has zero (0) dependencies on other software.</p>

<p>If this is ‚Äúhard‚Äù to do, demand better features from your language designers.</p>

<p>N.B. calling a function creates a hard-wired dependency.</p>
<ol>
  <li>The name of the function is (usually) hard-wired into the calling code.</li>
  <li>The CALL is (usually) implemented using a global variable (The Stack).  Using an implicit stack creates a dynamic dependency chain.</li>
</ol>

